UADataType.Description: This enumeration indicates the function of a specific feedstock.

Field.Name: Undefined
Field.Description: The function of the feedstock is unknown.

Field.Name: Main
Field.Description: The feedstock is used for production and is part of the finished part.

Field.Name: Ancillary
Field.Description: The feedstock is used for production but removed before the part is finished.

Field.Name: Consumable
Field.Description: The feedstock is consumed during the production e.g., process gas.

The MachineIdentificationAMType of the Additive Manufacturing information model holds static data which shall uniquely identify an AM machine among a pool of the AM machine operating entity.

The AdditiveManufacturingType represents the entire additive manufacturing interface of this information model. It is the entry point to the OPC UA interface of an AM machine and provides a basic structure. An instance of this type aggregates all information related to one AM machine.

A string containing a unique production number of the manufacturer of the MachineryItem. The global uniqueness of the serial number is only given in the context of the manufacturer, and potentially the model. The value shall not change during the life-cycle of the MachineryItem.
